{"title_page": "1927\u201328 FC Basel season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[FC Basel]]\n| logo               = \n| season             = 1927\u201328\n| chairman           = From 8 July to 15 September 1927<br />{{Flagicon|SUI}} Karl Junker<br />From 15 September<br />{{Flagicon|SUI}} [[Karl Ibach (footballer)|Karl Ibach]] \n| mgrtitle           = \n| manager            = \n| stdtitle           = Ground\n| stadium            = [[Landhof]], [[Basel]]\n| league             = [[1927\u201328 Swiss Serie A|Serie A]]\n| league result      = '''Group Stage:''' 3rd\n| cup1               = [[Swiss Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = Round of 64\n| league topscorer   = [[Karl W\u00fcthrich]] (8)\n| season topscorer   = [[Karl W\u00fcthrich]] (8)\n| highest attendance = 3,500 on 9 October 1927<br />vs [[FC Nordstern Basel|Nordstern Basel]]<br />and on 29 April 1928<br />vs [[BSC Old Boys|Old Boys Basel]]\n| lowest attendance  = 1,500 on 22 January 1928<br />vs [[FC Concordia Basel|Concordia Basel]]\n| average attendance = 2,700\n| prevseason         = [[1926\u201327 FC Basel season|1926\u201327]]\n| nextseason         = [[1928\u201329 FC Basel season|1928\u201329]] \n}}\n\nThe '''[[FC Basel]] 1927\u201328 season''' was their thirty fifth season since the clubs foundation on 15 November 1893. The club's new chairman was Karl Junker took over the presidency from Carl Burkhardt at the AGM on 8 July 1927. However Junker only remained as president until 15 September, then [[Karl Ibach (footballer)|Karl Ibach]] took over for his third period. FC Basel played their home games in the [[Landhof]] in the district Wettstein in Kleinbasel.\n\n== Overview ==\nBasel played a total of 27 matches in their 1927\u201328 season. 16 of these were in the domestic league, one was in the [[Swiss Cup]] and 10 were friendly matches. Of these 10 friendlies four were played at home in the [[Landhof]] and six were away games. Apart from the away game against [[FC Mulhouse|Mulhouse]] all other matches were in Switzerland.\n\nProbably one of the biggest highlights during these friendly games, was the fixture in the [[Landhof]] against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], who had just won the [[English Football League]] championship that season. The game attracted 8,000 supporters, but Basel lost the comparison against the english champions by two goals to nil. Both goals were scored by [[Dixie Dean]].<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-fcb-everton-1927/28\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=29381 | title = FC Basel - Everton FC 0:2 (0:1) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 16 November 2019}}</ref> Dean's greatest point of note is that he is still the only player in English football to score 60 league goals in one season and [[1927-28 in English football|this (1927\u201328)]] was the season in that he accomplished this record.<ref name=\"English League Leading Goalscorers 1889-2007\">{{cite web | first = | last = James M. Ross | title = English League Leading Goalscorers 1889\u20132007 | url = http://rsssf.com/tablese/engtops.html | publisher = Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation | accessdate = 16 November 2019}}</ref> At that the end of that season he was 21 years old.\n\nThe [[1927\u201328 Swiss Serie A]] was divided into three regional groups, each group with nine teams. Basel were allocated to the Central group together with the other three local clubs [[FC Concordia Basel|Concordia Basel]], [[FC Nordstern Basel|Nordstern Basel]] and [[BSC Old Boys|Old Boys Basel]]. The other five teams allocated to this group were [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys Bern]], [[FC Bern]], [[FC Aarau|Aarau]], [[FC Grenchen|Grenchen]] and [[FC Solothurn|Solothurn]]. The teams that won each group continue to the finals and the last placed teams in the groups had to play a barrage against relegation.  FC Basel played a good season, won ten matches, one was drawn and they suffered five defeats. Basel scored 27 goals and conceeded 21. With 21 points they ended the season in third position, two points behind group winners and local rivals Nordstern.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-bilanz-Saison 1927/28\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/bilanz?saison=1927/28 | title = Bilanz - Saison 1927/28 | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2018-11-16}}</ref>\n\nIn this season [[Swiss Cup]] Basel were drawn against [[SC Young Fellows Juventus|Young Fellows Z\u00fcrich]] in the first round and were eliminated because they lost 0\u20131.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-cup 1927/28\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=29399 | title = FC Basel - FC Young Fellows Z\u00fcrich 0:1 (0:0) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2018-11-16}}</ref>\n\n== Players ==\n;Squad members\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Ernst Christ]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Arthur Fahr]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Ernst Zorzotti]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Armando Ardizzoia]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Jakob B\u00fcrgin]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=FRG |pos=DF |name= [[Hermann Enderlin]] (II)}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Peter Riesterer]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Max Galler]] (II) }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Georg Heimann]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Otto Meier]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Paul Schaub]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Emil Arlt]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |nam