 in Transportation Management {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Placements ==\n\n\nIn 2019, UPES had '''560+ recruiters''' on campus and placed '''94%''' of employability-seeking students in leading national and international organisations including '''[[Accenture]], [[Adani Group|Adani]], [[Amazon.com|Amazon]], Anand & Anand, [[Ashok Leyland]], [[Baker Hughes]], [[BYJU'S|Byjus]], [[Decathlon]], [[Dell|Dell R&D]], [[Deloitte]], [[ExxonMobil|Exxon Mobil]], [[Ernst & Young|EY]], [[FedEx]], [[General Motors]], [[Halliburton|Haliburton]], [[Indian Navy]], [[Infosys]], [[L&T Technology Services|L&T,]] [[LinkedIn]], [[Maruti Suzuki]], [[Nestl\u00e9|Nestle]], [[ONGC]], Protiviti Global, [[Reliance Industries|Reliance]], [[Schlumberger]], [[Surana and Surana Moots|Surana & Surana]], [[Swiggy]], [[Vedanta Desika|Vedanta]]''', etc.\n\nIn 2020, one of the students, Saksham Kumar, from B. Tech Computer Science Engineering, received the '''highest package of INR 44 LPA''' so far, from a leading gaming company in the Netherlands. Kamal Dua, Abhishek Paharva and Kartik Singh, also from the School of Computer Science, have each landed a package of INR 30 LPA. '''UPES School of Design has closed with 100 % placements''' in record time with an average CTC of INR 6.34 LPA.\n<br />\n\n== Specialization-specific rankings == \n\n=== '''School of Business''' ===\n\n* NIRF Rank 56\n* '''Ranked No. 1 private institute'''     in Uttarakhand*\n* Ranked among top '''15 MBA     institutes''' in North India*\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>By Outlook-iCare India MBA Ranking 2020\n\n* '''IACBE''' accreditation     for '''MBA OG''' and '''MBA LSCM'''\n\n=== '''School of Engineering''' ===\n\n* B.Tech. Chemical Engineering     (Refining & Petrochemicals) and B.Tech. Automotive Design Engineering     are NBA accredited.\n\n=== '''CTF purpose''' ===\nflag: MIC{50met1me5_w1k1_w0rk5_f0r_u5}\n\n== See Also ==\n\n* [[University of Technology and Management]]\n* [[Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee]]\n* [[List of universities in India]]\n* [[List of business schools in Asia]]\n* [[University Grants Commission (India)]]\n\n==References==\nEligibility, Application Form, Admit Card Etc.<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-admission UPES Admission Process]</ref>\nHow to Apply for UPES application Form<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-application-form UPES Application Form Procedure]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official}}\n\n{{Dehradun}}\n{{Universities in Uttarakhand}}\n{{Colleges Under HERS}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Petroleum and Energy Studies}}\n[[Category:Universities in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Law schools in India]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Petroleum engineering schools]]\n[[Category:Institutions of Petroleum in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian University}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Primary sources|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = University of Petroleum & Energy Studies (UPES) \n|image_name     = \n|motto          = \n|mottoeng       = University with a purpose\n|established    = 2003\n|chancellor     = Dr. S J Chopra\n|vice_chancellor= Dr. Sunil Rai\n|undergrad      = \n|city           = [[Bidholi]], Via Prem Nagar, [[Dehradun]]\n|state          = [[Uttarakhand]]\n|country        = India\n|students       =\n|free_label     = \n|free           = \n|type           = Private University<ref name=\"upes.ac.in\">{{cite web|url=http://www.upes.ac.in/accreditations-recognitions|title=Accreditations & Recognitions|website=www.upes.ac.in |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131119091256/http://www.upes.ac.in/accreditations-recognitions |archivedate=19 November 2013 }}</ref>\n|campus         = [[Suburb]]an,{{convert|42|acre|ft2}}\n|affiliations   = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]], [[Department of Scientific and Industrial Research (India)|DSIR]], [[IGNOU]], [[Association of Indian Universities|AIU]], [[International Association of Universities|IAU]], [[Bar Council of India|BCI]]<ref name=\"upes.ac.in\"/>\n|website        = {{URL|http://www.upes.ac.in/}}\n|coor           ={{Coord|30|24|57.38|N|77|58|1.24|E|display=inline, title}}\n|logo= \n}}\nThe [[University of Petroleum and Energy Studies]] was established in 2003 through the UPES<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/|title=UPES University in Dehradun For Admission in MBA, LLB, B.tech, M.tech|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Act, 2003, of the State Legislature of [[Uttarakhand]]. The University is sponsored by Hydrocarbon Education Research Society (HERS), which is registered under the \u2018Societies Registration Act XXI of 1860\u2019 (Registration No. S-41894 of 2002). UPES is maintained by the [[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]] (UGC) under Section 2(f) of the UGC Act, 1956. The University functions under the ambit of its Act, Statutes, Rules and Regulations.\u00a0 It has also ensured due internal compliance to its obligations towards [[Right to Information Act|RTI]], Anti Ragging, [[Community service register|CSR]] and other regulations framed by the statutory authorities from time to time.\n\nUPES is a UGC-recognized university and has received a 5-star rating for both employability (placements) and campus facilities and a 4-star rating for teaching by the internationally acclaimed QS Ratings. It offers industry-aligned and specialised graduate and postgraduate programs through its eight schools, viz., School of Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-engineering|title=School of Engineering : Best School For Engineering in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, School of Computer Science<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-computer-science|title=School of Computer Science {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, School of Design,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-design|title=School of Design : Best Design University in Dehradun, India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> School of Law<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-law|title=Law School: Best Law University For Legal Studies in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, School of Business<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-business|title=School of Business Management : Business School For MBA & Economics - UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, School of Health Sciences<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-health-sciences|title=School Of Health Sciences - Health Science Course Info {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, School of Smart Agriculture <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-smart-agriculture|title=School of Smart Agriculture {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>and School of Modern Media<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-modern-media|title=School of Modern Media {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>. \n\nUPES offers 25% scholarship on tuition fees to all girl students for the complete program duration. It has undertaken several initiatives towards empowering women of all age groups through its CSR wing. \n\nUnder the UPES School of Engineering, B. Tech. students can pursue additional specialisations in latest technologies such as [[artificial intelligence]], [[Machine learning|Machine Learning]], [[Internet of things|IoT]], [[Data analysis|Data Analytics]] and [[Blockchain]]. The School also initiated a [[Diploma]] in [[Management|Business Management]] program for its [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] students. This course provides basic management skills and can be undertaken by the interested students along with their B. Tech program. \n\nUPES has collaborated with Coursera<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coursera.org/|title=Coursera {{!}} Build Skills with Online Courses from Top Institutions|website=Coursera|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, enabling its students to have free access to over 3800 global courses. Students can choose from 190 world renowned universities and industry partners such as [[Google]], [[IBM]], [[BCG]], [[Amazon Web Services]], etc.\n\n=== Global Exposure ===\nUPES graduate students get 50% waiver on PG programs tuition fees in over 22 UPES partner institutions in [[London]], [[Berlin]], [[Canada]] ([[Vancouver]] or [[Toronto]]), [[Singapore]] and [[Dublin]]. UPES students enrolling in the year 2020 can study overseas for four weeks in partner institutions, without any additional tuition fee. The 4-week study abroad program gives students exposure to global [[Expert|experts]], [[culture]], and situations. Students stand to benefit from lectures and seminars by expert faculty, notable guest speakers connected to industry and leading professional practitioners in their field, practical group work and exercises and visits to relevant industry and design studios.\n\n=== Placement Support ===\nUPES alumni get placement support for up to 5 years, post their graduation from the University. Support also comes in the form of [[Business incubator|incubation]] and funding up to Rs.10 lakh and workspace support in key cities. Alumni also have the advantage of a 35% scholarship on tuition fees for post-graduation at academic partner institutes abroad.\n\n==History and governance==\nUPES started with an interim campus in [[Dehradun]] in August 2003 with 3 courses, 224 students and 15 faculty members. Since then, it has expanded its offerings from hydrocarbons and allied areas to multidisciplinary areas of [[Energy]] / [[Information technology|IT]] / [[Transport|Transportation]] to provide industry aligned education. Today, UPES has two sprawling campuses \u2013 one at [[Bidholi]] and other at Kandholi \u2013 offering more than 80 industry-aligned courses ([[graduate]]{{dn|date=April 2020}}, [[Postgraduate education|post graduate]] and [[Doctorate|doctoral]] programs) to approximately 12,000+ students in the high growth sectors like [[Energy]], [[Infrastructure]], [[Transport|Transportation]], [[Information technology|Information Technology]], [[Electronics]], [[Design]], [[Business]], [[Public policy|Public Policy]], [[Legal Studies (law journal)|Legal Studies,]] etc. through its constituent schools. \n\nThe university has been accredited by the [[National Board of Accreditation]] (NBA) for Automotive Design Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/b-tech-automotive-design-engineering|title=Automobile Design Course: Automotive Engineering Schools in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> and Chemical Engineering (Specialisation: Refining and Petrochemicals) program. Moreover, UPES Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/ucie|title=UPES Centre For Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE)|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> (UCIE) has been recognised as an [[Business incubator|incubator]] by the [[Government of Uttarakhand]].\n\n=== '''UPES has following Statutory Authorities:''' ===\na. Board of Governors - Highest Regulatory Body to lay down policies, approve Budget/Annual Report, make, amend or repeal Statutes and Rules, etc.\n\nb. Board of Management - Principal Executive Body to approve senior appointments, \ufb01x emoluments of employees, approve infrastructural requirements, prepare annual accounts through Finance Committee, accept donations, enter into contracts, select common seal, make rules, etc.\n\nc. Academic Council - Principal academic body to coordinate and exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University\n\nd. Finance Committee - Principal \ufb01nancial body to take care of \ufb01nancial matters, prepare annual accounts and \ufb01nancial estimates, etc.              \n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|'''BOARD OF GOVERNORS'''\n\n'''UPES''' \n\n'''1st September 2018 - 31st August 2021'''\n|-\n|'''MEMBER SECRETARY'''\n\n'''Dr. Sunil Rai'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/messages-from-leader/vice-chanellors-message|title=Dr. Sunil Rai|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nVice Chancellor\n\nUniversity of Petroleum & Energy Studies\n\nEnergy Acres,P.O Bidholi Via Prem Nagar\n\nDehradun-248007\n|-\n|'''Ms Nandita Abra<u><span lang=\"EN-IN\"></span></u>ham''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pearlacademy.com/|title=Best College in India for Design & Fashion, Business & Media Courses|website=Pearl Academy|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nPresident\n\nPearl Academy\n\nA-21/13, Naraina Industrial Area, Phase II\n\nNear Shadipur Metro Station\n\nNew Delhi-110028\n|-\n|'''Mr Rajat Mukherjee'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaitanco.com/people/rajat-mukherjee|title=Rajat Mukherjee - Practices, Education & Recognitions|website=Khaitan & Co|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nPartner, Merger and Acquisition Practice Group\n\nKhaitan& Co.Law Firm, Ashoka Estate, 12th Floor, \n\n24 Brakhamba Road, New Delhi-110001\n|}\n\n== Awards and accolades ==\n\n* Leading university for international student experience at the UniAgents Annual Summit 2019\n* \u2018Excellence in Open & Distance Education\u2019 award at the World Education Summit 2019\n* Blackboard Catalyst Award for student success for Team Career Services at TLC Asia 2019\n* 'Best Academic-Industry Interface' by DNA (a leading Indian media house) in 2018\n* \u2018Best Industry-Academia Interface\u2019 at the 12th World Education Summit by Digital Learning & Elets Technomedia Pvt. Ltd. in 2018\n* \u2018Best University for Placements and Employability\u2019 by Times Now - National Education Excellence Award 2018\n* \u2018Great Place to Study\u2019 as per the Great Indian Institutes 2018 list by Forbes India\n* Ranked amongst top 30 world\u2019s best universities for Oil, Gas and Petroleum engineering by CEO World Magazine (USA) in 2017\n* International Accreditation Council for Business Education (IACBE) accredited MBA programmes (2017)\n* \u2018Best Training Institute Award\u2019 for the Port and Shipping Management programme at International SHIPTEK conference held in Dubai in 2016\n* Five stars for employability and campus facilities and four stars for teaching methodologies by globally acclaimed QS Ratings in 2016\n* \u2018University with Best Industry Academic Partnership\u2019 by India Today TV-Higher Education Excellence Awards \n* \u2018India\u2019s Best University for Innovation and Value based Education\u2019 by the Corporate Council for Leadership & Awareness (CCLA)\n\n=== PERSONAL COUNSELING ===\nUPES has a team of professionals including a full-time psychological counsellor to provide group as well as one to one counselling to students. Difficulties in academics and learning are dealt with through faculty mentors. The Department of Student Engagement and Experience works closely with the students to ensure a wide range of initiatives and activities for engaging them throughout the academic year.\n\n=== '''HEALTH AND MEDICAL SERVICES''' ===\nThe University provides its students first-aid support in the Infirmary. It is also equipped with [[ambulance]] [[Casualty evacuation|evacuation]] and two male and two female doctors to provide medical support to the students. [[Medical assistant|Medical assistance]], which is beyond the infirmary, is facilitated through a high-tech medical ambulance that has emergency management facilities. All the registered students in UPES are medically insured for a sum of INR 100,000. The insurance also covers road accident causality.\n\n=== '''FINANCIAL SUPPORT''' ===\nUPES extends [[Investor|financial support]] to the registered students on merit and means. At the time of admission, students are offered fee-relaxation based on their Class X and XII marks. It continues further based on marks scored by the students in their semester examination. The university has extended financial support to the students who are unable to pay the tuition fee on account of having lost any of the earning parents after their enrolment in UPES. Fee waiver is extended to [[Uttarakhand]] domicile students. Starting 2020, UPES has introduced a special scheme to promote higher education for girls by extending a 25% scholarship on their tuition fees for the complete program duration. \n\n=== '''REMEDIAL COACHING''' ===\nUnderstanding the importance of supporting the students to overcome their learning difficulties and gain confidence and interest in learning, remedial classes are planned and organised each year. The remedial classes are conducted for the students whose performance is not up to the mark, i.e., for the students who secure less than 40% marks in Mid-Term Examination. These classes help the slow learners to fill the gaps in the teaching learning process, which may be due to their slow learning pace, lack of understanding, lack of motivation to practice the problems etc. and ultimately enhance their learnings and skills, resulting in improvement in their performance.\n\n=== SPORTS ACTIVITIES ===\nAt UPES, students participate in a variety of games and sports that are organised at regular intervals in the university \u2013 UPES Annual Athletics Meet, Intra Mural Tournaments (All Sports), Inter-University Participation, Yoga and Meditation and Khel Utsav \u2013 UPES Sports Festival.\n\n=== CULTURAL ACTIVITIES ===\nUPES under the aegis of the Office of Student Engagement and Experience organises Freshers\u2019 Party and the '''Annual Cultural Festival \u2013 Uurja, which gives a platform to students to showcase their talents.''' Freshers\u2019 parties, to officially welcome the first-year students, are hosted by second-year students, organised by School Cultural Convener under the supervision of the office of Student Engagement and Experience. Uurja is the annual cultural festival and is celebrated for two days at the UPES Campus. Wow Wednesdays is a mid-week activity that allows students to unwind. This is planned to break the monotonous routine by providing students a platform to showcase their talent. Other prominent cultural and co-curricular events include Ignite, Hackathon, Design Fest, and Nitro RC Championship. \n<br />\n\n=== [[National Service Scheme|NATIONAL SERVICE SCHEME]] ===\nThe National Service Scheme (NSS) has been in operation in UPES since April 2018. The fundamental objective of the NSS is to awaken and enrich the social consciousness of students. The scheme provides an opportunity for students to engage in constructive social action, programs, develop co-operative team spirit and gain skills in democratic leadership quality.\n\nStudent of UPES are the primary beneficiary of the program by way of development of their perception about the community, their skill in performing specific jobs, and in developing the qualities of a leader, an organiser, and an administrator and the overall development of their personality as a whole. Through NSS, they get opportunities to see the community closely and thus get an experience of human nature in relation to their environment. This is how the NSS program aims to make the youth better citizens through \u2018Development of their Personality through Community Service\u2019. The University has also adopted several schools in villages and suburbs to impart primary and higher education and computer literacy. Students continuously participate in tree plantation drives, donation drives, rainwater harvesting, ''Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan'' and women\u2019s empowerment initiatives.\n\n=== '''UPES CENTRE FOR INNOVATION AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/ucie|title=UPES Centre For Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE)|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE) is a Business Incubator (BI) with focus on the technology sectors in [[Delhi]] [[NCR Corporation|NCR]] and [[Uttarakhand]] region belt. The mandate of the Centre is to assist the UPES community entrepreneurs (faculty, staff, alumni and students) as well as the external community entrepreneurs, commercialise their product/service ideas and/or accelerate their growth. The key technology focus areas are: [[Transport|Transportation]], [[Infrastructure]], [[E-commerce]], [[Education]], [[Energy]], [[Information technology|IT]] / ITES Gaming and Animation Cloud Computing, [[Biotechnology]], [[Energy technology|Energy Technology]], [[Food Processing Technology Building|Food Processing Technology]], Retail Technology and [[Fashion design|Fashion Technology]]. \n\nUCIE is a member of University Business Incubator (UBI) Global, which provides the centre a unique opportunity to understand, explore and visualize the state and impact of India's incubation ecosystem in a more efficient way. \n\nUCIE conducts a series of events with its network comprising local community, Departments of State Government, NGOs, Confederation of Indian Industry (CII), Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce & Industry (FICCI), PHD Chamber of Commerce by providing information about UCIE and its activities to build mutual cooperation and growth of entrepreneurship in the Uttarakhand region. \n\n==Location==\nUPES is situated in [[Dehradun]], the capital of the state of [[Uttarakhand]], India. The sprawling 44-acre University is divided into two campuses \u2013 UPES Bidholi, known as Energy Acres and UPES Kandoli, known as Knowledge Acres. \u00a0\n\n== Schools ==\n\n=== '''School of Health Sciences'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-health-sciences|title=School Of Health Sciences - Health Science Course Info {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> ===\nThe School of Health Sciences provides specialist health sciences programs as follows: \n\n==== '''Department of Allied Health Sciences''' ====\n\n===== '''UG PROGRAMS''' =====\n\n* B.Sc (Food, Nutrition and Dietetics) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/bsc-food-nutrition-and-dietetics|title=B.sc. in Food, Nutrition and Dietetics {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n* BBA (Hospital and Healthcare Management)  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/bba-hospital-and-healthcare-management|title=BBA Healthcare Management {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n* B. Optometry<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/b-optometry|title=B. Optometry - Admission, Fee, Curriculum {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n* B. Physiotherapy <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/b-physiotherapy|title=B. Physiotherapy - Admission, Fee, Curriculum {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n* B. Sc. (Microbiology) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/b-sc-microbiology|title=B.Sc. Microbiology - Admission, Fee, Curriculum {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n===== '''PG PROGRAMS''' =====\n\n* M. Sc. (Microbiology) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/m-sc-microbiology|title=M.Sc. Microbiology - Admission, Fee, Curriculum {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n* M. Sc. (Nutrition and Dietetics) <ref>{{Cite we