ol of Smart Agriculture gives students access to technologies ranging from Internet of Things to Big Data, AI Sensors to Unmanned Aerial Vehicles and GPS Robotics. The syllabus is as per ICAR guidelines and Convergence of Tech with Agriculture.\n\n'''SPECIALISED PROGRAMS'''\n\n* '''B. Sc. (Hons.) Agriculture, Duration - 4 years'''\n\nT<span lang=\"EN-GB\">UPES is situated in Dehradun, the capital of the state\nof Uttarakhand, India. The sprawling 44-acre University is divided into two\ncampuses \u2013 UPES Bidholi, known as Energy Acres and UPES Kandoli, known as\nKnowledge Acres. \u00a0</span>he curriculum comprises the study of agronomy, horticulture, plant pathology, animal sciences, and are supplemented by field visits and experiential learning. \n\n* '''B. Tech. Food Technology, Duration - 4 years'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/btech-food-technology|title=B. Tech Food Technology : Admission, Courses & Eligibility {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n<span lang=\"EN-GB\">UPES is situated in Dehradun, the capital of the state\nof Uttarakhand, India. The sprawling 44-acre University is divided into two\ncampuses \u2013 UPES Bidholi, known as Energy Acres and UPES Kandoli, known as\nKnowledge Acres. \u00a0</span>\n\nThe programme deals with the safety, quality assurance, distribution of food products and study of food processing plant operations. \n\n* '''M. Sc. Ag. (Agronomy), Duration - 2 years'''\n\nThe programme focusses on research in areas including Precision Agriculture and Smart Agriculture. \n\n<br />\n\n=== '''School of Modern Media''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-modern-media|title=School of Modern Media {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> ===\nThe School of Modern Media is equipped with labs, PCR (Production Control Room), Audio Recording Studio, Editing Lab, Photography Lab etc for the students. It offers the followin