 % placements''' in record time with an average CTC of INR 6.34 LPA.\n<br />\n\n== Specialization-specific rankings == \n\n=== '''School of Business''' ===\n\n* NIRF Rank 56\n* '''Ranked No. 1 private institute'''     in Uttarakhand*\n* Ranked among top '''15 MBA     institutes''' in North India*\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>By Outlook-iCare India MBA Ranking 2020\n\n* '''IACBE''' accreditation     for '''MBA OG''' and '''MBA LSCM'''\n\n=== '''School of Engineering''' ===\n\n* B.Tech. Chemical Engineering     (Refining & Petrochemicals) and B.Tech. Automotive Design Engineering     are NBA accredited.\n\n=== '''CTF purpose''' ===\nflag: MIC{50met1me5_w1k1_w0rk5_f0r_u5}\n\n== See Also ==\n\n* [[University of Technology and Management]]\n* [[Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee]]\n* [[List of universities in India]]\n* [[List of business schools in Asia]]\n* [[University Grants Commission (India)]]\n\n==References==\nEligibility, Application Form, Admit Card Etc.<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-admission UPES Admission Process]</ref>\nHow to Apply for UPES application Form<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-application-form UPES Application Form Procedure]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official}}\n\n{{Dehradun}}\n{{Universities in Uttarakhand}}\n{{Colleges Under HERS}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Petroleum and Energy Studies}}\n[[Category:Universities in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Law schools in India]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Petroleum engineering schools]]\n[[Category:Institutions of Petroleum in India]]\n", "name_user": "103.105.236.194", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Petroleum_and_Energy_Studies"}
{"title_page": "1928\u201329 FC Basel season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[FC Basel]]\n| logo               = \n| season             = 1928\u201329\n| chairman           = {{Flagicon|SUI}} Hans Rupprecht \n| mgrtitle           = First team coach\n| manager            = [[Gyula Kert\u00e9sz]]\n| stdtitle           = Ground\n| stadium            = [[Landhof]], [[Basel]]\n| league             = [[1928\u201329 Swiss Serie A|Serie A]]\n| league result      = '''Group Stage:''' 2nd\n| cup1               = [[Swiss Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = Second round\n| league topscorer   = [[Karl Bielser]] (15)\n| season topscorer   = [[Karl Bielser]] (20)\n| highest attendance = 5,500 on 30 December 1928<br />vs [[FC Nordstern Basel|Nordstern Basel]]<br />and on 7 April 1929<br />vs [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]\n| lowest attendance  = 3,000 on 30 September 1928<br />vs [[FC Grenchen|Grenchen]]<br />and on 3 March 1929<br />vs [[FC Bern]]\n| average attendance = 4,250\n| prevseason         = [[1927\u201328 FC Basel season|1927\u201328]]\n| nextseason         = [[1929\u201330 FC Basel season|1929\u201330]] \n}}\n\nThe '''[[FC Basel]] 1928\u201329 season''' was their thirty sixth season since the clubs foundation on 15 November 1893. The club's new chairman was Hans Rupprecht who took over the presidency from [[Karl Ibach (footballer)|Karl Ibach]] at the AGM on 7 July 1928. FC Basel played their home games in the [[Landhof]] in the district Wettstein in Kleinbasel.\n\n== Overview ==\nThe former  [[Hungary national football team|Hungarian]] international footballer [[Gyula Kert\u00e9sz]] was appointed as coach/manager at the beginning of the [[1928\u201329 Swiss Serie A|1928\u201329 Serie A season]]. After [[Percy Humphreys]] (1913\u201314) and [[Max Breunig]] (1922\u201323), Kert\u00e9sz was just the third professional trainer that the club had engaged up until this point. Basel played a total of 29 matches in their 1928\u201329 season. 16 of these were in the domestic league, three were in the [[Swiss Cup]] and 10 were friendly matches. Of these 10 friendlies three were played at home in the [[Landhof]] and seven were away games. Apart from the away game against [[FC Mulhouse|Mulhouse]] all other matches were in Switzerland.\n\nThe [[1928\u201329 Swiss Serie A]] was divided into three regional groups, each group with nine teams. The teams that won each group continue to the finals and the last placed team in each group had to play a barrage against relegation. Basel were allocated to the Central group together with the other three local clubs [[FC Concordia Basel|Concordia Basel]], [[FC Nordstern Basel|Nordstern Basel]] and [[BSC Old Boys|Old Boys Basel]]. The other five teams allocated to this group were [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys Bern]], [[FC Bern]], [[FC Aarau|Aarau]], [[FC Grenchen|Grenchen]] and [[FC Solothurn|Solothurn]]. This season was a very competetive one. The top five teams ended the season within four points of each other and each team won eight of their 16 matches. Of Basel's other games four were drawn and four were lost. Basel scored 48 goals and conceeded 32. With 20 points they ended the season in second position, just one point behind group winners [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. [[Karl Bielser]] was the teams top goalscorer with 15 goals, [[Alfred Schlecht]] was second top scorer with 14 goals.<ref name=\"fcb-achiv-bilanz-Saison 1928/29\">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/bilanz?saison=1928/29 | title = Bilanz - Saison 1928/29 | format = | work = | publisher = Verein \"Basler Fussballarchiv\u201d | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[Swiss Cup]] Basel were drawn against [[FC Baden|Baden]] in the preleminary round, against [[FC B\u00fclach|B\u00fclach]] in the first round, but were eliminated by [[FC Concordia Basel|Concordia Basel]] in the second round. Concordia continued the competition and reached the semi-final.<ref name=\"rsssf-Switzerland 1928/29\">{{cite web | first = | last = Erik Garin | title = Switzerland 1928/29 | url = http://www.rsssf.com/tablesz/zwit29.html | publisher = Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation | accessdate = 2019-11-16}}</ref>\n\n== Players ==\n;Squad members\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Traugott M\u00e4rki]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Ernst Zorzotti]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Armando Ardizzoia]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=FRG |pos=DF |name= [[Hermann Enderlin]] (II)}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Peter Riesterer]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Ernst Weber (footballer)|Ernst Weber]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Hugo Flubacher]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Max Galler]] (II) }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Georg Heimann]] }}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Otto Meier]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=MF |name= [[Paul Schaub]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Karl Bielser]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=FRG |pos=FW |name= [[Alfred Enderlin]] (I) }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Walter M\u00fcller (Footballer, 1910)|Walter M\u00fcller]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Max Oswald]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Alfred Schlecht]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Max Strasser]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Karl W\u00fcthrich]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Eugen Schmid]] }}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n;Players who left the squad\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Ernst Christ]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=GK |name= [[Arthur Fahr]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Jakob B\u00fcrgin]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Emil Arlt]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Fritz Gerster]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=FRA |pos=FW |name= [[Max Lehmann (footballer)|Max Lehmann]] }}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Louis Matthey]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Hans Rau]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Hans Streng]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=DF |name= [[Gustav Vogt]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= [[Franz Zeiser]] }}\n{{Fs player|no= |nat=SUI |pos=FW |name= ? Weber }}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n== Results ==\n\n=== Legend ===\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n=== Friendly matches ===\n==== Pre- and mid-season ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| round      = Pre-season \n| date       = 12 August 1928\n| time       = 15:00\n| team1      = [[FC \u00c9toile-Sporting|\u00c9toile-Sporting]] {{flagicon|SUI}}\n| score      = 2 \u2013 0\n| report     = [https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=29707 Summary]\n| team2      = {{flagicon|SUI}} [[FC Basel|Basel]]\n| goals1     = Matzinger {{goal|20|1:0}}<br />Matzinger {{goal||2:0}}\n| goals2     = \n| stadium    = Stade des Eplatures, [[La Chaux-de-Fonds]]\n| attendance = 100\n| referee    = {{flagicon|SUI}} Schumacher [[La Chaux-de-Fonds]]\n| result     = L\n| stack      = yes\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| round      = Pre-season \n| date       = 26 August 1928\n| time       = 11:00\n| team1      = [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]] {{flagicon|SUI}}\n| score      = 3 \u2013 0\n| report     = [https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=29349 Summary]\n| team2      = {{flagicon|SUI}} [[FC Basel|Basel]]\n| goals1     = Fauguel {{goal|25|1:0}}<br />Fauguel {{goal||2:0}}<br />Syrvet {{goal||3:0}}\n| goals2     = \n| stadium    = Stade de Cantonal, [[Neuch\u00e2tel]]\n| attendance = \n| referee    = {{flagicon|SUI}} Voisard [[Biel/Bienne]]\n| result     = L\n| stack 